# Cloud agent mandatory startup - read this first

Read this file first on a cloud agent VM. It is short on purpose.

## Automatic setup via Cursor saved environment

This repo no longer commits `.cursor/environment.json`, so Cursor Cloud Agents use the environment saved in Cursor. Configure the saved environment install command as:

```bash
bash ./.cursor/setup-agent.sh
```

This runs on VM startup, installing bun and all dependencies automatically.

## If setup didn't run automatically

If you're in a session where setup didn't run, manually execute:

```bash
cd /workspace
bash ./.cursor/setup-agent.sh
source ~/.bashrc
```

## Verify setup

Check that setup worked:

```bash
which bun      # Should show /home/ubuntu/.bun/bin/bun
bun --version  # Should show version number
```

## Working directory convention

**ALWAYS run commands from `/workspace` (repo root).**

This is a turborepo monorepo - turbo handles workspace dependencies automatically.

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT - from repo root (turbo handles everything)
cd /workspace
bun run build
bun run typecheck
bun run lint

# ❌ WRONG - changing into subdirectory or using --cwd
cd /workspace/apps/web && bun run build
bun run build --cwd apps/web
```

Turbo will figure out which packages need to run and in what order.

## Package installation convention

**ALWAYS install latest version** unless a specific version is required.

Use bun's workspace filtering to add packages to specific apps:

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT - install latest from repo root using --filter
cd /workspace
bun add @some/package@latest --filter apps/web

# Alternative: use --cwd if filter doesn't work
bun add @some/package@latest --cwd apps/web

# ❌ WRONG - manually editing package.json
# Don't manually edit package.json to add dependencies with hardcoded versions
```

## Self-improvement protocol

After completing any task, if you encountered issues with:
- Missing environment setup
- Unclear documentation
- Confusing instructions
- Repeated mistakes

**You MUST update the relevant documentation:**
- This file (`00-cloud-agent-mandatory.mdc`)
- Setup script (`.cursor/setup-agent.sh`)
- Other rule files in `.cursor/rules/`

Add learnings so the next agent doesn't face the same issues.

## Checklist before starting work

- [ ] Verify bun works: `which bun && bun --version`
- [ ] Currently in repo root: `pwd` shows `/workspace`
- [ ] If bun not found: Run setup manually (see above)

Setup should run automatically via the Cursor saved environment, but verify before proceeding.

## Completing your work (Cloud Agents)

**You MUST run `git add`, `git commit`, and `git push` before ending your response when you have made code changes.** Do not leave changes only in the working tree. Do not end your turn without pushing.

```bash
git add <changed-files>
git commit -m "descriptive message"
git push
```

- Use the existing branch (e.g. `cursor/...`) — do not push to `main` directly
- See [.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc](.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc) for full workflow (PRs, branch naming)

